# kube2docs routes all AI calls through litellm — set the env var for whichever
# provider --model points at. See https://docs.litellm.ai/docs/providers for the
# full list. You can also pass --api-key / --api-base on the CLI to override.

# Anthropic
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# OpenAI
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# OpenRouter
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# Google Gemini
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...

# Ollama (local) — override base URL if Ollama is not on the default host
# OLLAMA_API_BASE=http://localhost:11434

# Self-hosted OpenAI-compatible (vLLM, LM Studio, LocalAI) — use --api-base or set OPENAI_API_BASE
# OPENAI_API_BASE=http://localhost:8000/v1
